<%!-- Developer docs (a kit page). The page takes the same full max-w-6xl
footprint as a profile page (a wide content column + a right rail) instead of
the old narrow, centered 48rem strip. The 4-column split gives the docs body
more room than before while leaving a slim rail for credentials and the
project links. The horizontal page-nav stays at the top of the content card so
it is the first thing on a phone, never buried under the body in the rail. --%>
<div class="py-6">
  <header class="mb-6">
    <.link
      :if={@page != "index"}
      navigate={~p"/developers"}
      class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-600 hover:text-brand-700 dark:text-slate-400 dark:hover:text-brand-300"
    >
      ← {gettext("Developers")}
    </.link>
    <h1 class="mt-1 text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">{@page_title}</h1>
  </header>

  <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-4">
    <%!-- min-w-0: below md the grid is a single implicit `auto` track, so a long
    code line or URL in the docs would force this column past a phone viewport. --%>
    <div class="min-w-0 md:col-span-3">
      <.card>
        <nav class="mb-6 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-4 gap-y-2 border-b border-slate-100 pb-4 text-sm font-semibold dark:border-slate-800">
          <.link
            :for={{slug, label} <- @nav}
            href={if(slug == "index", do: ~p"/developers", else: ~p"/developers/#{slug}")}
            class={nav_class(@page == slug)}
          >
            {label}
          </.link>
        </nav>

        <div class="markdown text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200">
          {raw(@body)}
        </div>
      </.card>
    </div>

    <aside class="space-y-6">
      <%!-- A logged-in developer reading the docs gets one-click access to the
            pages where credentials actually live, instead of hunting through
            the profile settings sidebar for them. English labels to match the
            English-first docs (gettext would leave the rail half-German). --%>
      <.card :if={@conn.assigns[:current_user]}>
        <.section_title>Your account</.section_title>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm font-medium">
          <li>
            <.link
              navigate={~p"/access_tokens"}
              class="text-brand-600 hover:text-brand-700 dark:text-brand-400 dark:hover:text-brand-300"
            >
              Your access tokens
            </.link>
          </li>
          <li>
            <.link
              navigate={~p"/developers/apps"}
              class="text-brand-600 hover:text-brand-700 dark:text-brand-400 dark:hover:text-brand-300"
            >
              Your apps
            </.link>
          </li>
          <li>
            <.link
              navigate={~p"/connected_apps"}
              class="text-brand-600 hover:text-brand-700 dark:text-brand-400 dark:hover:text-brand-300"
            >
              Connected apps
            </.link>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </.card>

      <%!-- The invitation to participate, on every docs page: the repository and
            where to file bugs and feature requests. Pull requests welcome. --%>
      <.card>
        <.section_title>Project</.section_title>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm font-medium">
          <li>
            <.link
              href="https://github.com/wintermeyer/vutuv"
              class="text-brand-600 hover:text-brand-700 dark:text-brand-400 dark:hover:text-brand-300"
            >
              GitHub repository
            </.link>
          </li>
          <li>
            <.link
              href="https://github.com/wintermeyer/vutuv/issues"
              class="text-brand-600 hover:text-brand-700 dark:text-brand-400 dark:hover:text-brand-300"
            >
              Bug reports and feature requests
            </.link>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
          A project by developers, for developers. Pull requests are very welcome.
        </p>
      </.card>
    </aside>
  </div>
</div>
